The State visit follows attacks on foreign owned shops in the country, and retaliatory attacks on South African businesses based in Nigeria. The death toll from the violent looting of foreign owned shops in Gauteng province, now stands at 11.

The Presidency says the visit is aimed at reinforcing the strong bonds between the two countries.  

President Cyril Ramaphosa's spokesperson, Khusela Diko, says the two leaders are committed to finding a lasting solution... --SABC--